    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmNotes": "<p>&lt;@Compendium[sfrpg.rules.aKqRtg165rAly1Cc]{Poisons}</p>\n<p><em>Track the progress in the details tab in \"Base Value\". 0; Healthy, 5; Dead.</em></p>\n<p><em>To keep the affliction type a secret, renaming the item is suggested. This does not prevent the player from looking at the details tab to learn the affliction type.</em></p>\n<h2>@Compendium[sfrpg.equipment.bzR8Q6y0X4FE0jTF]{Shadow Essence}</h2>\n<p><strong>Type&nbsp;</strong>poison (injury);&nbsp;<strong>Save&nbsp;</strong>Fortitude DC 18<br /><strong>Track&nbsp;</strong>Strength;&nbsp;<strong>Frequency&nbsp;</strong>1/round for 6 rounds<br /><strong>Effect&nbsp;</strong>At the impaired state, the penalties from the weakened state become permanent until the victim benefits from a @Compendium[sfrpg.spells.usqy3VusjjgEnM9N]{Restoration} spell (see page 374).<br /><strong>Cure&nbsp;</strong>1 save</p>\n<p><em>Modifiers currently do not effect Ability DCs.</em></p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-underline-header);\">Strength Poison Track</h2>\n<p><strong>Healthy&mdash;Weakened&mdash;Impaired&mdash;Staggered&mdash;Immobile&mdash;Dead</strong></p>\n<h3>Weakened</h3>\n<p>The victim takes a &ndash;2 penalty to Strength-based ability checks, attack rolls, damage rolls, and skill checks, and the DCs of his spells and special abilities decrease by 2. The victim&rsquo;s total carrying capacity is reduced by two-thirds (minimum 1 bulk), and he gains the @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.OwZA6flUQPH0jPA0]{Encumbered} condition regardless of how much he is carrying.</p>\n<h3>Impaired</h3>\n<p>The victim takes an additional &ndash;2 penalty to the affected checks, rolls, and DCs, and he gains the @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.11k3ObUIXEYFGrg9]{Overburdened} condition regardless of how much he is carrying.</p>\n<h3>Staggered</h3>\n<p>The victim is @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.aAQ6SW6iK0EVq8Ce]{Staggered}, except he can still take a purely mental full action.</p>\n<h3>Immobile</h3>\n<p>The victim is helpless and can take only purely mental actions.</p>\n<h3>Dead</h3>\n<p>The victim dies.</p>",
      "gmnotes": "",
